description: Ben Grimm has bad luck. He never got the grades, he never got the girl and Cosmic Rays shoved the ugly stick down his throat. But where did this stroke of bad luck come from? Take a look behind Ben's bathroom door, find out just what's underneath those rocks of his and rediscover why the Thing is the coolest and grumpiest super hero on Earth! description:
A new edition of the classic collection featuring PREACHER SPECIAL: SAINT OF KILLERS #1-4, PREACHER SPECIAL: THE STORY OF YOU-KNOW-WHO and PREACHER SPECIAL: THE GOOD OLD BOYS, starring Arseface, the Saint of Killers, and Jody and T.C., the evil bastards of Angelville who haunted the Preacher's childhood.

Back Blurb

THE BAD, THE WORSE, AND THE UGLY

In his quest to track down an AWOL God and force Him to answer for his failings, the Reverend Jesse Custer has met a host of strange characters --- and it's no surprise to learn that they each have a story to tell.

ANCIENT HISTORY collects those stories from some of PREACHER's most colorful personalities, as originally presented in the three PREACHER SPECIALS: "Saint of Killers" lays out the complete origin of Custer's supernatural nemesis, stretching from the frozen plains of the American West to the hottest corners of Hell; "The Good Old Boys" looks back on a happier time of Jody and T.C., those rascally rednecks from bayou country, as they gleefully despoil every action-movie clich in the book while offhandedly foiling an international terrorist's plans; and "The Story of You-Know-Who" ventures into the backwoods of suburban angst to relate the tragic, farcical saga that gave the world Arseface.

ANCIENT HISTORY is the fourth volume in the PREACHER saga, one of the most celebrated comics titles of the late 1990s. Created by the writer Garth Ennis and artist Steve Dillon, this modern American epic of life, death, love and redemption is also packed with sex, booze, blood and bullets --- not to mention angels, demons, God, vampires and deviants of all stripes --- making for one of the most viscerally appealing tales to ever see four-color print.

description: Though the New Republic is thriving, there are still many who remain true to the spirit and evil designs of Emperor Palpatine. So when Luke Skywalker, the New Republic's greatest hero and sole Jedi master, decides to marry Mara Jade, the woman who was formerly Emperor Palpatine's personal assassin and executor of the Empire's will, you can be sure that somebody is going to raise their hands in protest!
name: Part 1 of 4

description: As the wedding approaches, Luke Skywalker has a troubling vision: somewhere in their future, a dark hand is grasping at him and his new wife, Mara Jade. But nothing can shake the young Jedi Knight's resolve, not a solemn ceremony of Jedi accepting the Union, nor even a night of carousing and revelry deep within the city canyons of Coruscant.

description: As Luke and Mara gather their friends about them and prepare to share their vows, another vow is also closer to being fulfilled: Imperial Moff Takkar pledges the destruction of this wedding, a travesty and an insult to the memory of the once-great Empire!

description: Wedding Day! But as the guests are taking their places, the Imperial's disruption of the festivities begins! Swoop riders are raiding the building and a madman with a vest-full of explosives is threatening to take the entire building down! Who can save the saviors of the galaxy?
